SUPIR is_accelerate_available MPS workaround.

kijai/ComfyUI-SUPIR loads CLIP weights via accelerate's
init_empty_weights + set_module_tensor_to_device path, which leaves
any buffer not present in the loaded state-dict (e.g. CLIPTextModel's
position_ids) on the meta device. The conditioner.to(device) call
then crashes with "Cannot copy out of meta tensor". Force the
load_state_dict fallback by flipping the accelerate gate to False.
The node's docstring advertises accelerate as "slightly faster" -- not required.

Generated against kijai/ComfyUI-SUPIR rev fe0d660f7c02556f6ae9affa3357d871358ebea7.
If a future supirRev bump moves the line, regenerate this diff.

--- a/nodes_v2.py
+++ b/nodes_v2.py
@@ -17,7 +17,7 @@
 try:
     from accelerate import init_empty_weights
     from accelerate.utils import set_module_tensor_to_device
-    is_accelerate_available = True
+    is_accelerate_available = False
 except:
     pass
